1
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:20,040
Young Lady.

2
00:00:21,640 --> 00:00:22,560
Young Lady.

3
00:00:25,480 --> 00:00:26,320
Young Lady.

4
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:29,360
Are you in there, Young Lady?

5
00:00:30,680 --> 00:00:32,200
Open the door, Young Lady.

6
00:00:32,200 --> 00:00:33,530
=Cases Between Us=

7
00:00:33,530 --> 00:00:34,480
Young Lady.

8
00:00:35,160 --> 00:00:36,000
Young Lady.

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:38,060
=Episode 15=

10
00:00:38,060 --> 00:00:39,720
Can you hear me, Young Lady?

11
00:00:40,880 --> 00:00:42,080
Open the door.

12
00:00:43,040 --> 00:00:43,800
Young Lady.

13
00:01:04,640 --> 00:01:06,680
- Why is it all cordoned off?
- This haunted house.

14
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:08,520
Just like back then...

15
00:01:10,790 --> 00:01:11,970
The police are here. Quick.

16
00:01:12,480 --> 00:01:13,120
Officer,

17
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:13,960
can we go in?

18
00:01:13,960 --> 00:01:14,720
No.

19
00:01:14,752 --> 00:01:16,120
It's a crime scene, not a theater.

20
00:01:16,120 --> 00:01:16,790
- Officer.
- Yes.

21
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:18,370
Everyone without business here,
stand back.

22
00:01:18,384 --> 00:01:19,000
You, too.

23
00:01:20,480 --> 00:01:21,240
Wan'er,

24
00:01:21,240 --> 00:01:22,720
people are watching.

25
00:01:22,720 --> 00:01:23,680
How would it look

26
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:24,840
if I let you in?

27
00:01:26,040 --> 00:01:27,080
Where's Yuan Hong?

28
00:01:27,920 --> 00:01:29,000
I'm looking for him, too.

29
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:29,640
Hey.

30
00:01:29,640 --> 00:01:30,240
You lot,

31
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:31,280
keep watch.

32
00:01:31,280 --> 00:01:32,080
Nobody gets in.

33
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:32,600
Yes.

34
00:01:32,600 --> 00:01:33,880
Ungrateful brat.

35
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:35,880
Did you forget
who got you the consultant job?

36
00:01:36,400 --> 00:01:37,200
What are you doing?

37
00:01:37,200 --> 00:01:37,960
Are you threatening

38
00:01:37,960 --> 00:01:38,880
the police?

39
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:39,240
You!

40
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:40,600
Someone's assaulting an officer.

41
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,320
Officer,

42
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:43,640
I heard this place is haunted.

43
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:44,800
Could Bai Lu's death

44
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:45,960
have something to do with it?

45
00:01:45,984 --> 00:01:47,440
Why do you call it a haunted house?

46
00:01:47,440 --> 00:01:48,992
No. 33 used to belong to Wu Yingxiong.

47
00:01:49,024 --> 00:01:51,168
When Wu Sangui rebelled,
Wu Yingxiong was held hostage

48
00:01:51,170 --> 00:01:52,520
and executed by Emperor Kangxi.

49
00:01:52,520 --> 00:01:54,280
They say a woman
can be heard crying here

50
00:01:54,280 --> 00:01:55,640
every night.

51
00:01:55,640 --> 00:01:56,720
I've heard another story.

52
00:01:56,720 --> 00:01:58,400
Cao Xueqin once lived here, too.

53
00:01:58,400 --> 00:01:59,680
He died before finishing

54
00:01:59,680 --> 00:02:00,720
"Dream of the Red Chamber".

55
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:01,800
Enough.

56
00:02:01,840 --> 00:02:03,720
If you're making things up,
make them believable.

57
00:02:03,760 --> 00:02:05,520
Do you know
what era Cao Xueqin lived in?

58
00:02:05,520 --> 00:02:06,688
There you are, Consultant Zhao.

59
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:08,440
You scared me!

60
00:02:08,440 --> 00:02:09,120
Let's go.

61
00:02:09,168 --> 00:02:11,664
Bai Lu's death has to be connected
to this haunted house.

62
00:02:12,480 --> 00:02:13,560
The victim, Bai Lu.

63
00:02:13,560 --> 00:02:16,200
She locked herself in her room
after handing the baby to the nanny

64
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:17,240
at ten o'clock last night.

65
00:02:17,392 --> 00:02:18,448
At two in the morning,

66
00:02:18,450 --> 00:02:19,424
the baby needed feeding.

67
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:22,432
The nanny unlocked the door and found
Bai Lu hanging from the chandelier

68
00:02:22,432 --> 00:02:24,240
with a rope around her neck.

69
00:02:24,440 --> 00:02:25,640
So the moment the door opened,

70
00:02:25,640 --> 00:02:27,280
the body was hanging in midair.

71
00:02:28,800 --> 00:02:30,040
In midair?

72
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:31,560
Where's Yuan Hong?

73
00:02:32,760 --> 00:02:33,800
He's on leave.

74
00:02:33,800 --> 00:02:35,440
Before he left, he put me in charge

75
00:02:35,440 --> 00:02:37,080
of everything in Division Four.

76
00:02:37,080 --> 00:02:39,800
So you'll be working with me
on this case.

77
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,120
Working with you?

78
00:02:41,184 --> 00:02:42,800
More like you'll be working with me.

79
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,120
We'll work together.

80
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:45,680
We'll make a good team, right?

81
00:03:21,520 --> 00:03:22,560
What are you doing here?

82
00:03:22,560 --> 00:03:24,688
You didn't give me the exclusive
on the last case.

83
00:03:24,752 --> 00:03:26,480
You promised to make it up to me.

84
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:28,360
Now I have to sneak into crime scenes

85
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:29,920
on my own.

86
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:30,760
No.

87
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,540
That's not my fault.

88
00:03:32,560 --> 00:03:34,112
- You were too slow.
- I don't care.

89
00:03:34,640 --> 00:03:35,760
You're not shaking me off

90
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:36,840
this time.

91
00:03:36,840 --> 00:03:37,480
You...

92
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:39,160
Du,

93
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:40,360
what's going on here?

94
00:03:45,616 --> 00:03:46,880
The victim's left carotid artery

95
00:03:46,880 --> 00:03:48,240
and jugular vein were severed.

96
00:03:48,336 --> 00:03:48,896
There are also

97
00:03:48,912 --> 00:03:51,070
multiple ligature marks
of different depths on her neck.

98
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:52,480
The upper ones are deeper.

99
00:03:52,480 --> 00:03:54,672
It suggests the killer first
strangled her from behind

100
00:03:54,688 --> 00:03:55,720
with something thinner.

101
00:03:55,968 --> 00:03:57,600
There was something else
besides the rope?

102
00:03:58,640 --> 00:03:59,080
Look.

103
00:03:59,168 --> 00:04:00,784
There are two different kinds of marks.

104
00:04:00,816 --> 00:04:02,680
This one, running upward,

105
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:04,360
was caused by the hanging.

106
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:06,928
This one, running front to back,

107
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:08,920
was made when the killer strangled her
from behind.

108
00:04:08,920 --> 00:04:10,440
And although there wasn't much bleeding,

109
00:04:10,440 --> 00:04:11,720
the wound suggests

110
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:13,200
a thinner, sharper object.

111
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:15,040
Why are the marks different colors?

112
00:04:15,056 --> 00:04:16,920
The bluish bruising
happened while she was alive.

113
00:04:16,944 --> 00:04:18,450
The brown marks
were left after death.

114
00:04:18,464 --> 00:04:20,400
So what killed her?
Suffocation or blood loss?

115
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,160
An adult

116
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:22,600
needs to lose over 2.5 liters of blood

117
00:04:22,600 --> 00:04:23,670
before going into shock.

118
00:04:23,680 --> 00:04:25,520
This wasn't nearly enough.

119
00:04:25,680 --> 00:04:27,000
She died of suffocation.

120
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:28,720
There's no blood spatter.

121
00:04:29,160 --> 00:04:31,000
She was probably dead
before her throat was cut.

122
00:04:31,480 --> 00:04:34,240
The bedroom door, the balcony door,
and all the windows

123
00:04:34,520 --> 00:04:36,000
were locked.

124
00:04:36,600 --> 00:04:37,800
After ten last night,

125
00:04:38,040 --> 00:04:39,360
Bai Lu was alone

126
00:04:39,360 --> 00:04:40,200
in the room.

127
00:04:40,400 --> 00:04:41,560
A locked-room murder?

128
00:04:47,280 --> 00:04:49,240
What if the killer

129
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,720
threaded the rope
through the gap under the door

130
00:04:52,040 --> 00:04:53,760
and looped it around her neck?

131
00:04:53,760 --> 00:04:55,136
How do you explain the cutthroat?

132
00:04:55,360 --> 00:04:56,400
By your theory,

133
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,120
the killer used two different weapons.

134
00:04:58,120 --> 00:04:58,992
First, strangled her.

135
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,608
Then slit her throat to drain the blood.

136
00:05:00,610 --> 00:05:02,448
Then why didn't he use the blade
from the start?

137
00:05:04,880 --> 00:05:06,440
After she lost consciousness,

138
00:05:07,000 --> 00:05:09,080
the killer wasn't sure she was dead,

139
00:05:09,800 --> 00:05:10,960
so on the spur of the moment,

140
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:14,360
he used a thinner, sharper tool
to cut her throat.

141
00:05:15,240 --> 00:05:16,840
Something that was

142
00:05:16,840 --> 00:05:18,040
readily at hand.

143
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,280
A cello stand.

144
00:05:22,200 --> 00:05:23,200
Sheet music.

145
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:25,880
The murder weapon was the string.

146
00:05:27,008 --> 00:05:28,432
Bai Lu often practiced the cello

147
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:30,400
out on the balcony.

148
00:05:30,400 --> 00:05:31,872
After strangling her with the rope,

149
00:05:31,888 --> 00:05:34,000
the killer used a cello string
to slit her throat

150
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:34,840
and drain the blood.

151
00:05:34,944 --> 00:05:37,184
Then, afraid the murder weapon
would be found,

152
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:38,560
he took the cello with him.

153
00:05:38,960 --> 00:05:39,680
Case solved.

154
00:05:40,160 --> 00:05:42,040
If that's true,
that's pretty far-fetched.

155
00:05:42,040 --> 00:05:43,280
Enough for a front-page feature.

156
00:05:43,280 --> 00:05:44,160
The rope's so soft.

157
00:05:44,160 --> 00:05:45,632
How did the killer get it in here?

158
00:05:46,840 --> 00:05:48,120
Flapping your gum,

159
00:05:48,384 --> 00:05:50,720
yet the only thing that sounds plausible
is the cello string.

160
00:05:52,920 --> 00:05:53,880
Check the courtyard.

161
00:05:53,880 --> 00:05:55,072
See if there are any footprints.

162
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:57,480
What?

163
00:05:57,480 --> 00:05:58,360
You expect me to go?

164
00:06:05,880 --> 00:06:07,400
The bedding and furniture in this room

165
00:06:07,400 --> 00:06:10,920
aren't cheap.

166
00:06:10,920 --> 00:06:13,760
She had expensive taste.

167
00:06:13,824 --> 00:06:16,120
Are you here to cover the case,
or check out her bedroom?

168
00:06:16,120 --> 00:06:17,000
What do you know?

169
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,240
She hadn't worked in three years.

170
00:06:18,240 --> 00:06:19,200
Look at these.

171
00:06:19,200 --> 00:06:20,560
Why did all this money come from?

172
00:06:22,920 --> 00:06:23,560
Du.

173
00:06:24,000 --> 00:06:25,240
Go talk to Bai Lu's mother.

174
00:06:26,000 --> 00:06:27,520
You people are good at finding clues.

175
00:06:27,600 --> 00:06:28,940
When it comes to asking questions,

176
00:06:28,960 --> 00:06:29,800
who do you think

177
00:06:29,800 --> 00:06:30,760
ladies are more willing

178
00:06:30,760 --> 00:06:32,240
to confide in?

179
00:06:35,320 --> 00:06:36,280
You.

180
00:06:44,120 --> 00:06:44,920
Please have some tea.

181
00:06:49,680 --> 00:06:51,280
Lu is a celebrity.

182
00:06:51,400 --> 00:06:52,120
Of course,

183
00:06:52,440 --> 00:06:55,160
she had the very best of everything.

184
00:06:55,160 --> 00:06:57,440
My son-in-law owns
the Jingshi No. 1 Restaurant.

185
00:06:57,720 --> 00:07:00,240
He gives her 300 silver coins
every month.

186
00:07:02,400 --> 00:07:04,720
Were he and Bai Lu close?

187
00:07:05,960 --> 00:07:06,760
They were close.

188
00:07:08,040 --> 00:07:09,960
Lu's wedding

189
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:11,840
caused quite a stir in Beijing.

190
00:07:12,032 --> 00:07:14,448
She turned down high-ranking officials
and military commanders

191
00:07:14,480 --> 00:07:15,560
to marry him.

192
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:18,320
Doesn't that prove
how much they loved each other?

193
00:07:19,480 --> 00:07:20,440
Are you sure?

194
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:27,480
What do you mean?

195
00:07:29,560 --> 00:07:30,760
The shoe cabinet by the door.

196
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:32,440
The men's slippers
are on the bottom shelf.

197
00:07:32,695 --> 00:07:34,695
The few men's shoes that are left

198
00:07:34,720 --> 00:07:35,760
are old

199
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:36,960
and dusty.

200
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:39,008
They clearly haven't been worn
for quite some time.

201
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:42,240
Zhang Chengcai doesn't come home much,
does he?

202
00:07:43,720 --> 00:07:44,480
He's busy.

203
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:46,240
My ex-husband

204
00:07:46,240 --> 00:07:47,760
used to say the same thing.

205
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,240
Besides,

206
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:50,800
I heard

207
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:52,960
this is a haunted house.

208
00:07:56,160 --> 00:07:57,880
A man who truly loves his wife

209
00:07:58,240 --> 00:08:00,160
would never make her live here.

210
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,960
Lu and Chengcai

211
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:19,080
had been estranged for a long time.

212
00:08:19,360 --> 00:08:20,440
Why?

213
00:08:21,360 --> 00:08:24,120
Zheng Chengcai's a jerk.

214
00:08:24,880 --> 00:08:26,000
Before the wedding,

215
00:08:26,360 --> 00:08:27,520
he doted on her.

216
00:08:29,360 --> 00:08:30,520
He swore

217
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:33,000
she'd be the only woman he'd ever love.

218
00:08:33,680 --> 00:08:34,840
Once he had her,

219
00:08:35,960 --> 00:08:37,360
he drank himself senseless every day

220
00:08:39,600 --> 00:08:41,480
and practically moved
into the Eight Alleys.

221
00:08:42,120 --> 00:08:43,160
She put up with that?

222
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,360
She couldn't.

223
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,560
Lu wanted a divorce.

224
00:08:47,960 --> 00:08:51,040
But then she found out she was pregnant.

225
00:08:51,880 --> 00:08:55,120
That rascal wanted an heir. He got down
on his knees, begging her to stay.

226
00:08:55,640 --> 00:08:56,880
Lu was soft-hearted,

227
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,000
so she forgave him.

228
00:09:01,520 --> 00:09:02,360
Who would've thought

229
00:09:02,480 --> 00:09:04,384
that before she'd finished
her confinement,

230
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:07,600
he was seeing other women again?

231
00:09:07,600 --> 00:09:08,840
Can you call him human?

232
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,480
He's worse than an animal.

233
00:09:13,160 --> 00:09:14,840
Lu's health never recovered,

234
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:16,760
and remarriage became impossible.

235
00:09:17,440 --> 00:09:20,000
Zhang Chengcai's temper
only got worse.

236
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:22,200
He beat and cursed her every few days.

237
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,920
Last night, he came home

238
00:09:25,760 --> 00:09:27,400
and got furious

239
00:09:29,072 --> 00:09:30,760
because she didn't pour him any water.

240
00:09:32,480 --> 00:09:34,800
(Bai Lu)
Not even a glass of water?

241
00:09:34,800 --> 00:09:36,940
(Zhang Chengcai)

242
00:09:39,190 --> 00:09:39,940
Nice bed.

243
00:09:40,560 --> 00:09:42,720
Quit putting on airs.

244
00:09:44,240 --> 00:09:45,760
Who do you think you are?

245
00:09:46,120 --> 00:09:47,360
Other people may not know,

246
00:09:47,680 --> 00:09:48,800
but I do.

247
00:09:49,240 --> 00:09:51,840
That cup's British bone china.

248
00:09:51,840 --> 00:09:53,400
Royal Worcester.

249
00:09:54,240 --> 00:09:55,480
Worth five silver coins.

250
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:57,600
Bring me the money tomorrow morning.

251
00:09:57,800 --> 00:10:01,440
Or I'll sell your dirty little secrets
to the newspapers.

252
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:03,680
Let everyone in Beijing see

253
00:10:03,680 --> 00:10:05,240
whether you're a gentleman

254
00:10:05,240 --> 00:10:06,760
or a fake rich man.

255
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:09,520
Have I spoiled you too much?

256
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:11,920
You really think you're somebody?

257
00:10:13,320 --> 00:10:15,280
Who do you think you are?

258
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:17,600
Let go...

259
00:10:18,240 --> 00:10:18,840
Young Master.

260
00:10:18,840 --> 00:10:21,720
- Let go of her, Chengcai.
- Please let go, Young Master.

261
00:10:21,720 --> 00:10:22,400
Chengcai.

262
00:10:22,400 --> 00:10:23,720
You can't do that.

263
00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:24,160
Let go.

264
00:10:24,160 --> 00:10:24,800
Chengcai.

265
00:10:24,800 --> 00:10:25,360
Get lost!

266
00:10:25,560 --> 00:10:26,280
Chengcai.

267
00:10:26,560 --> 00:10:27,840
Zhang Chengcai, you beast!

268
00:10:27,840 --> 00:10:29,520
She's the mother of your child.

269
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:30,400
Zhang Chengcai,

270
00:10:30,400 --> 00:10:31,616
if you don't leave right now,

271
00:10:31,640 --> 00:10:33,040
I'm calling the police.

272
00:10:33,040 --> 00:10:34,800
Let go, Young Master.

273
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:36,920
Let go, Young Master.

274
00:10:37,680 --> 00:10:38,800
Let go.

275
00:10:38,800 --> 00:10:40,240
She's having trouble breathing.

276
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:45,560
What a spoilsport.

277
00:10:49,560 --> 00:10:50,440
Lu,

278
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:51,920
are you all right?

279
00:10:59,760 --> 00:11:00,680
See?

280
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:02,680
I told you there were footprints.

281
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,640
The killer definitely climbed up
from here.

282
00:11:04,752 --> 00:11:06,160
What do you think, Consultant Zhao?

283
00:11:10,352 --> 00:11:11,320
Only footprints coming in,

284
00:11:11,320 --> 00:11:12,280
none going out.

285
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:28,800
The back door is always left unlocked?

286
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:30,920
Last week, the Young Master
came home drunk.

287
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,760
The Young Lady wouldn't let him in.

288
00:11:32,760 --> 00:11:33,720
He got mad

289
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,040
and kicked the door in.

290
00:11:35,040 --> 00:11:37,080
He wouldn't let us repair it.

291
00:11:37,080 --> 00:11:38,880
He said it was to make sure

292
00:11:38,880 --> 00:11:40,320
we wouldn't lock him out again.

293
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:52,880
The killer came in
through the back door,

294
00:11:53,800 --> 00:11:55,080
went under the balcony,

295
00:11:55,080 --> 00:11:57,120
climbed up the drainpipe,

296
00:11:57,120 --> 00:11:58,800
and killed Bai Lu.

297
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:01,440
But the killer
didn't leave the same way.

298
00:12:01,920 --> 00:12:03,400
When the body was found,

299
00:12:03,800 --> 00:12:05,520
the bedroom door
was locked from the inside.

300
00:12:06,400 --> 00:12:07,720
When the body was found,

301
00:12:08,528 --> 00:12:10,040
the killer was still inside the room.

302
00:12:11,240 --> 00:12:12,120
Impossible.

303
00:12:12,120 --> 00:12:13,520
There's nowhere to hide.

304
00:12:32,600 --> 00:12:34,280
Didn't Bai Lu close the curtains
at night?

305
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:36,640
She never did.

306
00:12:36,840 --> 00:12:38,440
She said it felt stuffy
with them closed.

307
00:12:40,680 --> 00:12:42,320
Could the killer

308
00:12:42,640 --> 00:12:44,160
have been hiding behind the curtains?

309
00:12:46,192 --> 00:12:47,744
When you and Madam Bai found the body,

310
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:49,500
your attention would've been
on the victim.

311
00:12:49,560 --> 00:12:51,160
You wouldn't
have noticed that one curtain

312
00:12:51,170 --> 00:12:52,760
was sticking out further than the other.

313
00:12:52,775 --> 00:12:53,975
That's possible.

314
00:12:54,000 --> 00:12:55,840
But if that's what happened,

315
00:12:55,840 --> 00:12:57,560
when did the killer leave?

316
00:12:59,480 --> 00:13:01,040
After you and Madam Bai found the body,

317
00:13:01,104 --> 00:13:02,560
did either of you leave this room?

318
00:13:03,002 --> 00:13:04,482
I went downstairs to call the police.

319
00:13:04,560 --> 00:13:06,000
Madam stayed here, holding the child,

320
00:13:06,048 --> 00:13:07,400
until the police arrived.

321
00:13:11,081 --> 00:13:12,361
Then the killer never left.

322
00:13:12,480 --> 00:13:14,200
And there was nowhere to hide.

323
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:16,360
Could the killer have
just vanished into this air?

324
00:13:30,680 --> 00:13:31,880
What are you looking at?

325
00:13:33,480 --> 00:13:34,120
Look.

326
00:13:35,520 --> 00:13:36,360
Young Master Zhao!

327
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:37,920
It's high enough.

328
00:13:38,016 --> 00:13:39,200
It goes all the way through.

329
00:13:39,264 --> 00:13:40,480
Plenty of room inside.

330
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:42,240
A person could fit through with a cello.

331
00:13:43,400 --> 00:13:44,040
Come down.

332
00:13:45,560 --> 00:13:46,720
The killer escaped

333
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:48,520
through the chimney?

334
00:13:48,520 --> 00:13:49,720
When the maid opened the door,

335
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,880
the killer must've
hidden inside the fireplace,

336
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,280
then climbed up the drainpipe,

337
00:13:53,280 --> 00:13:54,720
and came down the drainpipe.

338
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:57,560
The killer knew the place well.
Must've been someone familiar.

339
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:59,040
According to Madam Bai,

340
00:13:59,104 --> 00:14:00,720
Bai Lu had stayed out of public life

341
00:14:00,720 --> 00:14:01,840
for three years.

342
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:04,360
That leaves only one person
with a reason to hate her.

343
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:06,040
Zhang Chengcai.

344
00:14:06,112 --> 00:14:07,280
He came back last night.

345
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:07,960
At six o'clock,

346
00:14:07,960 --> 00:14:09,632
he had a huge argument with Bai Lu.

347
00:14:09,760 --> 00:14:10,760
I'm not finished yet.

348
00:14:12,180 --> 00:14:14,580
(Interrogation Room)

349
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:17,640
Where were you

350
00:14:17,640 --> 00:14:18,600
at ten last night?

351
00:14:20,240 --> 00:14:20,680
Seriously?

352
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:22,840
Do you know who I am?

353
00:14:23,800 --> 00:14:24,800
Zhang Chengcai.

354
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:28,800
Boju

355
00:14:29,040 --> 00:14:30,400
is my brother.

356
00:14:30,962 --> 00:14:33,442
Jingshi No. 1 Restaurant VIP.

357
00:14:33,568 --> 00:14:34,400
You're arresting me?

358
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:35,960
Did you ask for his permission?

359
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:39,040
Do I need to ask?

360
00:14:39,040 --> 00:14:40,040
Go ahead.

361
00:14:58,360 --> 00:14:59,040
Hello?

362
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:00,960
I'm Zhao Shaoshang.

363
00:15:01,240 --> 00:15:02,600
Do you have a younger brother?

364
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:03,520
Zhang Chengcai.

365
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:04,760
He runs a restaurant.

366
00:15:04,840 --> 00:15:06,336
Your father had an illegitimate son?

367
00:15:06,352 --> 00:15:08,360
Is that a secret I don't know?
Or am I mistaken?

368
00:15:11,880 --> 00:15:13,320
I'm not playing weiqi with you.

369
00:15:13,320 --> 00:15:15,400
Your skills are terrible.

370
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:17,000
Another day.

371
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:17,960
I've been busy.

372
00:15:17,960 --> 00:15:18,520
Alright.

373
00:15:19,240 --> 00:15:20,440
Say hi to Ms. Su for me.

374
00:15:20,640 --> 00:15:21,240
Bye.

375
00:15:28,544 --> 00:15:30,384
Your brother says he doesn't know you.

376
00:15:30,920 --> 00:15:32,520
You know Eldest Young Master?

377
00:15:34,360 --> 00:15:36,080
Where were you
at ten o'clock last night?

378
00:15:36,560 --> 00:15:38,560
Do you know
Young Master Zhang from Fengtian?

379
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:41,040
We're close. We
play tennis together all the time.

380
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:43,080
We're practically brothers.

381
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:45,330
Every time he comes to Beijing,
I'm the one who hosts him.

382
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:49,440
Quick.

383
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:50,240
Take the cuff off.

384
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:51,440
Well.

385
00:15:52,120 --> 00:15:53,920
We're all friends here.

386
00:15:54,520 --> 00:15:55,760
You see,

387
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:57,240
now we've become friends.

388
00:15:57,240 --> 00:15:57,960
How about this?

389
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:58,880
Come by

390
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:00,360
my restaurant sometime.

391
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:01,480
It's on me.

392
00:16:01,800 --> 00:16:02,640
Yang Dezhi.

393
00:16:03,520 --> 00:16:04,600
Yes, Young Master Zhao?

394
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:05,960
Beat him.

395
00:16:05,960 --> 00:16:06,640
Sorry?

396
00:16:06,704 --> 00:16:08,550
If anything happens,
I'll take responsibility.

397
00:16:08,576 --> 00:16:09,720
Your words, not mine.

398
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:10,720
Wait.

399
00:16:18,440 --> 00:16:19,880
You're finally useful for once.

400
00:16:19,880 --> 00:16:21,200
This is nothing.

401
00:16:21,200 --> 00:16:22,440
This is Mongolian wrestling.

402
00:16:22,440 --> 00:16:23,480
Let me show you

403
00:16:23,480 --> 00:16:24,800
the Bannermen's style.

404
00:16:24,800 --> 00:16:26,640
No, no. I'll talk.

405
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:28,120
I was drinking on Yangmeizhuxie Street

406
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,280
all night last night.

407
00:16:29,680 --> 00:16:30,520
Any witnesses?

408
00:16:30,520 --> 00:16:31,600
Yes.

409
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:32,680
Several.

410
00:16:42,780 --> 00:16:44,080
(Division Four Chief's Office)

411
00:16:44,080 --> 00:16:45,280
He didn't kill her.

412
00:16:45,640 --> 00:16:46,360
Why?

413
00:16:46,880 --> 00:16:47,800
Zhang Chengcai

414
00:16:48,680 --> 00:16:49,520
has thin,

415
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:50,480
weak limbs.

416
00:16:51,160 --> 00:16:52,280
He's frail.

417
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:55,160
Chimney?

418
00:16:55,160 --> 00:16:55,760
Drainpipe?

419
00:16:55,760 --> 00:16:56,920
He couldn't climb either one.

420
00:16:57,600 --> 00:16:58,760
He's a drunkard.

421
00:16:58,760 --> 00:16:59,840
Alcohol dependence.

422
00:17:00,280 --> 00:17:02,440
His hands shake
when pointing at someone.

423
00:17:03,376 --> 00:17:05,680
Even if he wanted to kill,
he wouldn't have the strength.

424
00:17:06,440 --> 00:17:08,000
I'm innocent, officer!

425
00:17:08,000 --> 00:17:09,600
Zhang Chengcai didn't kill anyone.

426
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:12,032
Ma'am, you'll need to register first.

427
00:17:12,064 --> 00:17:13,320
- Then we'll take your report.
- What?

428
00:17:13,320 --> 00:17:15,210
- I want your person in charge.
- No. What's this about?

429
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:16,600
Who comes here for no reason?

430
00:17:16,600 --> 00:17:17,080
Wait.

431
00:17:17,080 --> 00:17:18,820
- Ma'am.
- Who is making all that racket?

432
00:17:19,200 --> 00:17:20,240
(Mei Fen)
So much noise.

433
00:17:20,240 --> 00:17:21,240
Who's in charge here?

434
00:17:21,240 --> 00:17:22,200
I am.

435
00:17:22,440 --> 00:17:23,320
Who are you?

436
00:17:23,320 --> 00:17:24,320
This is Consultant Zhao.

437
00:17:24,760 --> 00:17:26,640
Consultant Zhao
of the police department.

438
00:17:27,320 --> 00:17:27,720
Good.

439
00:17:27,720 --> 00:17:28,440
Whoever you are.

440
00:17:28,440 --> 00:17:29,760
Zhang Chengcai didn't kill anyone.

441
00:17:29,824 --> 00:17:30,544
Release him.

442
00:17:30,680 --> 00:17:31,160
Hold on.

443
00:17:31,520 --> 00:17:32,440
Who are you?

444
00:17:32,440 --> 00:17:33,320
I'm his wife.

445
00:17:33,320 --> 00:17:34,640
Isn't his wife Bai Lu?

446
00:17:34,640 --> 00:17:35,680
Only on paper.

447
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:38,240
I'm the woman he truly loves.

448
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:44,280
I can testify for him.

449
00:17:44,280 --> 00:17:45,880
Zhang Chengcai is innocent.

450
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:46,920
I drove him

451
00:17:46,920 --> 00:17:48,160
to the Eight Alleys from his home

452
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:49,720
last night.

453
00:17:49,840 --> 00:17:52,112
(What happened that night)
This is a signed statement

454
00:17:52,144 --> 00:17:52,920
from every girl

455
00:17:52,920 --> 00:17:54,920
who drank with him last night.

456
00:17:55,680 --> 00:17:56,920
Seven eyewitnesses.

457
00:17:58,160 --> 00:17:59,240
Seven?

458
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:04,080
No need to show me that.

459
00:18:04,432 --> 00:18:05,800
Witness statements can be bought.

460
00:18:06,600 --> 00:18:08,000
Perjury isn't hard.

461
00:18:08,544 --> 00:18:10,016
Unless you're willing to pay them

462
00:18:10,016 --> 00:18:11,120
to change their statements.

463
00:18:11,184 --> 00:18:12,720
Otherwise, you'd better release him.

464
00:18:13,020 --> 00:18:15,200
(End of Episode 15)

465
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:17,640
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

466
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:19,180
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

467
00:18:19,180 --> 00:18:20,430
♪However, the world changes♪

468
00:18:20,430 --> 00:18:22,350
♪You'll still be by my side♪

469
00:18:22,350 --> 00:18:24,040
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

470
00:18:24,040 --> 00:18:25,610
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

471
00:18:25,610 --> 00:18:27,180
♪If this is my final chapter♪

472
00:18:27,180 --> 00:18:29,680
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
